From: Sergey Fedorov <barracuda@macos-powerpc.org>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 14:42:06 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 32/67] feat(macos): configure summary for the frontend +
 optional standalone .app bundle

1. Configuration summary now reports the native macOS frontend choice, the
   frontend ObjC++ compiler (with a warning if the default modern GCC is used
   instead of gcc-4.2), the ObjC++ standard, and the bundle setting.

2. CONTOUR_MACOS_BUNDLE=ON (default OFF) builds a self-contained Contour.app:
   the target becomes a MACOSX_BUNDLE with a minimal Info.plist and INSTALL_RPATH
   @executable_path/../Frameworks, and an install(CODE fixup_bundle) step copies
   every non-system dylib the binary needs (MacPorts libstdc++/libgcc_s, freetype,
   harfbuzz, fontconfig, libunicode, yaml-cpp, ...) into Contents/Frameworks and
   rewrites load paths, so the app runs with MacPorts deactivated. System
   frameworks are left as-is. Bundling the correct libstdc++/libgcc_s also makes
   the two-libstdc++ runtime issue moot for the bundled app. Default OFF keeps the
   plain bin/ install for normal MacPorts builds.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
